30/09/2005
VATICAN CITY -- Serbian President Boris Tadic met with Pope Benedict XVI in the Vatican Thursday (29 September) and expressed his hopes for a papal visit as soon as arrangements can be made.
Tadic, the first Serbian president to meet with a pope, said they discussed Kosovo, issues of regional stability, and factors linked to instability.
(Danas, Politika - 30/09/05;
Tanjug, Beta, B92, RTS, BBC - 29/09/05)
